Cut the top and bottom off the @courgette{1}, slice into long strips about ½ cm thick. Cut the top off the @red pepper{1} and remove the seeds, slice into long strips. Drain and thoroughly rinse the @green lentils{1%cup}.

Heat a #frying pan{} with @olive oil{1%tsp} over high heat. Fry the strips of courgette in the pan in batches, remove to one side. Repeat with the red pepper strips.

> Tip: You want the veg to char slightly, which is easier with less oil.

Make a vinaigrette with @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, the @thyme{4%sprigs} leaves, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few grinds of @black pepper{}.

> Tip: Pull your fingers along the thyme stalks to remove the leaves.

Drain and rinse the lentils then mix with the courgette, red pepper, @wild rocket{1/2%bunch} and the vinaigrette. Taste for seasoning and add more salt or pepper as required.

Cut the @halloumi{1%block} into slices 1cm thick. Coat in @olive oil{1 1/2%tsp} and the zest from the @lemon{1/2}.

Heat a frying pan over medium heat. Cook the halloumi for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side, until golden brown.

Divide the salad between your #bowls{} and top with the halloumi.